    "date": "2021-07-22T01:56:28Z",
    "text": "Rural America Health Corps Act\n\nThis bill establishes a student loan repayment demonstration program for eligible providers who agree to work for five years in a rural area with a shortage of primary, dental, or mental health care providers. For each year of this service, the Department of Health and Human Services must pay one-fifth of the principal and interest on a provider's qualifying loans, up to a maximum of $200,000."
  },
